<section id="home">
  <div class="card">
    <h2>What is Cyberbullying?</h2>
    <p>
      Cyberbullying is when someone uses the internet or digital devices to hurt,
      embarrass, or threaten another person.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>What should you do if you are bullied online?</h2>
    <p>
      If you are bullied online, do not reply to the bully because it can only make things worse. 
      Instead, you can block and report the person and save screenshots as evidence. 
      It is also important to tell a trusted adult or parent so they can help you handle the situation safely.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="tips">
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Why should kindness matter on the internet?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Kindness matters on the internet because real people are behind those screens, and hurtful words can affect their feelings and mental health.</li>
      <li>Being kind helps to create a safe and positive online environment where everyone can feel respected and supported.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="whys">
  <div class="card">
    <h2>5 Whys Analysis (Cyberbullying)</h2>

    <div class="why-box">
      <strong>Why 1:</strong> Why does cyberbullying happen?<br>
      <em>Answer:</em> Because some people want to hurt or control others online.<br>
      <strong>Solution:</strong> Promote kindness and awareness online.
    </div>

    <div class="why-box">
      <strong>Why 2:</strong> Why do people want to hurt others online?<br>
      <em>Answer:</em> They may feel insecure, angry, or want attention.<br>
      <strong>Solution:</strong> Teach emotional control and empathy.
    </div>

    <div class="why-box">
      <strong>Why 3:</strong> Why do they act differently online?<br>
      <em>Answer:</em> They feel anonymous and think there are no consequences.<br>
      <strong>Solution:</strong> Enforce stricter online rules and accountability.
    </div>

    <div class="why-box">
      <strong>Why 4:</strong> Why are consequences not always clear?<br>
      <em>Answer:</em> Not all platforms or schools respond quickly or properly.<br>
      <strong>Solution:</strong> Improve reporting systems and responses.
    </div>

    <div class="why-box">
      <strong>Why 5:</strong> Why don’t victims always report it?<br>
      <em>Answer:</em> They may feel scared, ashamed, or unsupported.<br>
      <strong>Solution:</strong> Create safe spaces and encourage speaking up.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="importance">
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Why should we take cyberbullying seriously?</h2>
    <p>
      We should take cyberbullying seriously because it can deeply affect a person’s mental health, 
      causing stress and anxiety. It can also impact their confidence and school performance, 
      so it’s important to stop it early and support those affected.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

